@startuml 03-act-rag-ingestion
title Movie Finder — Activity Diagram: RAG Ingestion Pipeline (Target Architecture)

skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam roundcorner 8
skinparam ArrowColor #555555
skinparam ActivityBackgroundColor #E8F5E9
skinparam ActivityBorderColor #388E3C
skinparam ActivityFontSize 12
skinparam ActivityDiamondBackgroundColor #FFF9C4
skinparam ActivityDiamondBorderColor #F57F17
skinparam NoteBackgroundColor #FFFDE7
skinparam NoteBorderColor #F9A825
skinparam PartitionBackgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam PartitionBorderColor #AAAAAA

|GitHub Actions (Parameterized Job)|
start
:Receive workflow_dispatch trigger\nor scheduled run;
:Read job parameters:\n  EMBEDDING_PROVIDER (openai/anthropic/ollama)\n  VECTOR_STORE (qdrant/pinecone/weaviate)\n  CHUNKING_STRATEGY (fixed/semantic/sentence)\n  ENV (dev/staging/prod)\n  BATCH_SIZE;

note right
  Issue #29 — parameterized job
  allows runtime provider + strategy
  selection without code changes
end note

|IngestionPipeline|
:EmbeddingProviderFactory.create(settings);
:VectorStoreFactory.create(settings);
:ChunkingStrategyFactory.create(settings);

note right
  Issue #42 / ADR-0008 —
  factories select the correct
  provider implementation based
  on EMBEDDING_PROVIDER env var
end note

|DatasetLoader|
:Locate CSV source (Kaggle / local path);
:Parse records (title, plot, genres, year, rating);
:Validate mandatory fields (skip malformed rows);

|ChunkingStrategy|
if (Strategy = semantic?) then (yes)
  :Segment using cosine similarity\nbetween consecutive sentence embeddings;
  note right
    Issue #31 — SemanticChunker
    preserves plot coherence
    better than fixed-size splits
  end note
else if (Strategy = sentence?) then (yes)
  :Group sentences into\nmax N-sentence windows;
else (fixed)
  :Split into fixed-size chunks\n(chunk_size=512, overlap=64);
endif
:Attach payload metadata\n(title, year, genres, imdb_id);

|EmbeddingProvider|
:Batch embed chunks\n(provider batch API, up to 2048 texts/call);

note right
  Batch embedding reduces API
  calls from N to ceil(N/2048)
end note

|VectorStoreProvider|
:Resolve collection name:\n{env}_movies (dev_movies / staging_movies / movies);

note right
  Issue #14 — environment-scoped
  collection name prevents
  cross-environment data leakage
end note

if (Collection exists?) then (no)
  :Create collection\n(dim from provider, cosine metric);
else (yes)
endif
:Batch upsert vectors\n(chunks + embeddings + payloads);

|IngestionPipeline|
:Compute IngestionMetrics\n(total, embedded, upserted, failed,\nduration_s, cost_usd, strategy, provider, env);

|GitHub Actions (Parameterized Job)|
:Write step summary (markdown metrics table);
:Upload JSON artifact (ingestion-metrics.json);

note right
  Issue #29 — step summary
  and artifact allow cost tracking
  and regression detection per run
end note

if (Success rate >= 99%?) then (yes)
  :Mark job PASSED;
  stop
else (no)
  :Mark job FAILED;
  :Alert via GitHub notification;
  stop
endif

@enduml
